courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of the courses, students should be able to:

1. Broaden and deepen their understanding of a real-world issue through problem-based and solution-oriented learning process
2. Apply and integrate the knowledge of social science and design thinking skills to create impactful solutions
3. Interact with relevant stakeholders (e.g. NGOs, industry practitioners and think tanks) in designing practical and innovative solutions for various social problems
4. Identify professional skills required in managing such an organization;
5. Demonstrate work attitudes, code of courtesy and sense of organizational affiliation to fulfil duties assigned to the internship position;
6. Identify own strengths and weaknesses with regard to employment in the sector;
7. Make in‐depth reflection on self‐development, host organization, own career and society with good reasons and illustrations provided.

